ges/Networking/Sources/Networking/Networking.swift:1:// Networking module for SwiftAI Boilerplate Pro\nPackages/Networking/README.md:3:HTTP client with interceptors, retry logic, response caching, and comprehensive error handling for SwiftAI Boilerplate Pro.\nPackages/Payments/README.md:3:RevenueCat wrapper for subscription management in SwiftAI Boilerplate Pro.\nPackages/DesignSystem/PROMPTS.md:15:> Replace the Aurora theme colors with my brand palette. Update `DSColors.swift` to change `accentPrimary`, `accentSecondary`, `background`, `surface`, and `textPrimary` for the `.aurora` case. Update `DSGradient.primaryLinear` for the Aurora case as well. Test in both the theme picker and a chat screen.\nPackages/Auth/README.md:3:Unified authentication with Apple, Google, and Email via Supabase Auth for SwiftAI Boilerplate Pro.\nPackages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/BrandConfig.swift:10:    public static let appDisplayName = \"SwiftAI Pro\"\nPackages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11y.swift:62:    /// Accessibility labels for chat interface\nPackages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11y.swift:89:        /// New chat button\nPackages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11y.swift:91:            label: \"New chat\",\nPackages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11y.swift:109:        /// Delete chat action\nPackages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Accessibility/A11y.swift:111:            label: \"Delete chat\",\nPackages/Core/PROMPTS.md:15:> Add a new deep link route to `DeepLinkBus` that opens a specific conversation by ID. Follow the existing deep link pattern in `Packages/Core/Sources/Core/DeepLink/`. The URL format should be `myapp://chat/{conversationID}`.\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/DeepLink/DeepLink.swift:5:    /// Navigate to chat with specific conversation\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/DeepLink/DeepLink.swift:6:    case chat(conversationId: String)\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/DeepLink/DeepLink.swift:17:        // Handle custom URL scheme: sai://chat?conversationId=debug-123\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/DeepLink/DeepLink.swift:20:            case \"chat\":\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/DeepLink/DeepLink.swift:25:                    AppLogger.debug(\"Parsed chat deep link: \\(conversationId)\", category: AppLogger.notifications)\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/DeepLink/DeepLink.swift:26:                    return .chat(conversationId: conversationId)\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/DeepLink/DeepLink.swift:28:                    AppLogger.debug(\"Missing or empty conversationId in chat deep link\", category: AppLogger.notifications)\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/DeepLink/DeepLink.swift:47:        case .chat(let conversationId):\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/DeepLink/DeepLink.swift:48:            return \"chat(conversationId: \\(conversationId))\"\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/Notifications/LocalNotificationTester.swift:66:        content.categoryIdentifier = \"chat.message\"\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/Notifications/NotificationCategoryClient.swift:27: * - Registers chat.reply category with text input and mark read actions\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/Notifications/NotificationCategoryClient.swift:51:        // Create chat.message category with text input and mark read actions\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/Notifications/NotificationCategoryClient.swift:53:            identifier: \"chat.reply\",\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/Notifications/NotificationCategoryClient.swift:61:            identifier: \"chat.markRead\",\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/Notifications/NotificationCategoryClient.swift:66:        let chatMessageCategory = UNNotificationCategory(\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/Notifications/NotificationCategoryClient.swift:67:            identifier: \"chat.message\",\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/Notifications/NotificationCategoryClient.swift:74:        let categories: Set<UNNotificationCategory> = [chatMessageCategory]\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/AppLogger.swift:9:    public static let subsystem = Bundle.main.bundleIdentifier ?? \"SwiftAI\"\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/AppLogger.swift:22:    /// Logger for feature operations (chat, settings, etc.)\nPackages/Core/Sources/Core/Core.swift:1:// Core module for SwiftAI Boilerplate Pro\nPackages/Core/README.md:3:Centralized error handling, structured logging, and functional result utilities for SwiftAI Boilerplate Pro.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_17","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"cd apps/waketask-iphone && sed -n '1,220p' Packages/DesignSystem/Sources/DesignSystem/Tokens/BrandConfig.swift\"","aggregated_output":"import SwiftUI\n\n/// Brand configuration for customization\n/// \n/// Buyers can modify these values to customize the app's branding.\n/// Changes here will be reflected throughout the app.\npublic struct BrandConfig {\n    \n    /// App display name shown in UI\n    public static let appDisplayName = \"SwiftAI Pro\"\n    \n    /// Accent color for highlights and CTAs\n    public static let accentColor: Color = DSColors.primary\n    \n    /// SF Symbol name for default avatar\n    public static let avatarFallbackSymbol = \"person.circle.fill\"\n    \n    /// App icon background color (for generated icons)\n    public static let appIconBackground: Color = DSColors.primary\n    \n    // MARK: - Customization Guide\n    \n    /*\n     HOW TO CUSTOMIZE YOUR BRAND\n     ============================\n     \n     1. App Display Name:\n        Change `appDisplayName` to your app's name\n        Example: \"MyAI Assistant\" or \"ChatBot Pro\"\n     \n     2. Accent Color:\n        Option A: Update the Primary color in Colors.xcassets\n        Option B: Set accentColor to a custom Color:\n            public static let accentColor = Color(red: 0.2, green: 0.6, blue: 1.0)\n     \n     3. Avatar Symbol:\n        Browse SF Symbols app and pick an icon:\n        Examples: \"sparkles\", \"brain.head.profile\", \"message.fill\"\n        Update `avatarFallbackSymbol` with the symbol name\n     \n     4. Color Scheme:\n        Edit Resources/Colors.xcassets to customize:\n        - Primary (brand color)\n        - BubbleUser (user message bubble)\n        - BubbleAssistant (AI message bubble)\n        - TextPrimary, TextSecondary (text colors)\n        - Background, Separator\n     \n     5. Typography:\n        Modify DSTypography in Typography.swift:\n        - Change font sizes\n        - Switch font design (.default, .rounded, .serif, .monospaced)\n        - Adjust line spacing\n     \n     All changes automatically apply throughout the app with no additional code changes needed.\n     */\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
