{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_38","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"cat > apps/waketask-iphone/SwiftAIBoilerplatePro/Resources/terms.md <<'EOF'\n# Terms of Service\n\n**Last Updated:** May 14, 2026\n\n## 1. Agreement\nBy using WakeTask, you agree to these Terms.\n\n## 2. Service Description\nWakeTask provides alarm, wake mission, wake-check, and reliability tracking tools intended to help users wake and start first-task execution.\n\n## 3. Accounts\nYou are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for activity on your account.\n\n## 4. Subscriptions and Billing\nPaid features may require a subscription. Subscriptions renew automatically unless canceled at least 24 hours before renewal, subject to Apple billing rules.\n\n## 5. Acceptable Use\nYou agree not to misuse the app, attempt to disrupt service operation, reverse engineer restricted components, or violate applicable law.\n\n## 6. Availability\nWakeTask may be updated, changed, or suspended. Alarm reliability depends on device state, permissions, and OS behavior.\n\n## 7. Disclaimer\nThe app is provided \\\"as is\\\" without warranties of uninterrupted operation or fitness for a particular purpose.\n\n## 8. Limitation of Liability\nTo the maximum extent permitted by law, WakeTask and its operators are not liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages.\n\n## 9. Termination\nWe may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms.\n\n## 10. Changes to Terms\nWe may update these Terms. Continued use after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.\n\n## 11. Contact\nFor support and legal inquiries: \"'`support@waketask.app`\nEOF'","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
